              'Static NAT — one-to-one mapping of private to public IP; used for servers that must be consistently reachable.',
              'Dynamic NAT — maps private IPs to a pool of public IPs; one-to-one but addresses assigned dynamically.',
              'PAT (Port Address Translation) / NAT Overload — maps many private IPs to one public IP using different ports; the most common form in home and office routers.',
